  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "A list of issues that are hard to solve because of how Sputnik works:\r\n\r\n**VM errors**\r\n\r\nThese are hard to solve because the error message we really want is somewhere deep in Sputnik's `Machine` that we have no control over. Usually the error just gets converted from an `ExitReason::Error(ExitError)` to an `ExitReason::Revert(ExitRevert)`.\r\n\r\n- [x] https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/issues/499\r\n- [x] https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/issues/476\r\n\r\n**Cheatcodes**\r\n\r\n- [ ] https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/issues/432: Can only be solved by changing the control flow of the EVM, which again, requires us to fork `Machine`",
